>
<p>
  Science fiction, fantasy, television, and film have been major influences throughout my
  life, particularly through gaming, online communities, and podcasting. However, storytelling
  and worldbuilding only became a much larger personal interest later on through podcasting
  and fandom communities.
</p>
<p>
  Working on shows such as The G&amp;T Show introduced me to books, audiobooks, long-form
  storytelling, and wider science fiction and fantasy communities that I had never really
  explored growing up. That experience gradually expanded my interests beyond simply watching
  television and films into storytelling, atmosphere, worldbuilding, character-driven
  narratives, and creative projects of my own.
</p>
<p>
  Many of the creative projects I work on today — particularly around Roll20 and Midnight
  Realm — have grown directly out of that later discovery of storytelling-focused media and
  communities.
</p>

